## Query builder = a nest (mirror the workout builder)

Layers, top-down (= workout nest, own product nouns):

**Query тЖТ Section тЖТ Breakdown тЖТ Subject тЖТ Measure** = Session тЖТ Block тЖТ Sequence тЖТ Exercise тЖТ Set.

- **Structure/feel тЙИ workout nest** тАФ same rails/chevrons/lock/More/`+ Add` DNA; accents from workout `layer` / `override` / set chip **by depth** via `qbTokens.ts` (`QB_TO_FORM`). Content inside nodes is analytics (not a Session field clone). Decision 12 overturned the provisional cool `queryLayer`.
- Every layer has a **hidden SQL meaning** (Query = FROM+window, Section = WHERE scope, Breakdown = GROUP BY, Subject = one PG + identity, Measure = op ├Ч field). SQL is taught by structure, never shown by default.
- **Ops live at the Measure leaf:** `sum ┬╖ avg ┬╖ max ┬╖ min ┬╖ count` ├Ч `reps ┬╖ time ┬╖ distance ┬╖ load ┬╖ sets`. e.g. "most reps in one set" = `max ├Ч reps`.
- v1 shape: **exactly one auto Section**; Breakdown wraps Subjects with **no nested Breakdowns**; Breakdown dims = `variation`/`tool`; **one PG per Subject** (complexes credit-each); per-Subject variations/tools are **soft, never enforced**.
- Engine is **client-side** group/aggregate over `v_log_set_facts` тАФ no new fact schema, no `saved_queries`/`008` until Nate asks.

## Dashboard direction (locked)

- **Subject first:** Primary Group(s) required; **facets** are shape-driven atomic fields (reps / time / distance / load / set count) тАФ show what was logged, never sum unlike units.
- **Scope:** nest labels + set type = query-global WHERE; **variations / tools = per-PG** (soft, never enforced). Not rival lenses.
- **Multi-PG:** one editable card per selected PG. **Category** = PG metadata for balance **saved views**, not a home-screen lens.
- **Read source:** `v_log_set_facts`; credit-each under the hood; complete logs only.

